    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@Haroenv @bobylito So I added the alias in webpack and now everything is working fine 👍\r\n```js\r\nresolve: {\r\n            extensions: ['.ts', '.js'],\r\n            alias: {\r\n                'react': 'preact-compat',\r\n                'react-dom': 'preact-compat'\r\n            }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n@bobylito I never had the issue with 2.0.2, and it is only ~~those two widgets~~ the one widget `MenuSelect` that the error comes up for, which I am not using by the way. [(update)](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues/2612#issuecomment-349061638)\r\n\r\nOh and @Haroenv, sorry I can't put up my code, I'm working with a private repo.",
